        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 12 at 6:52PM EDT by NWS Blacksburg VA</headline>
        <description>At 652 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
New Glasgow, or near Amherst, moving north at 5 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Amherst...
Clifford...
Lowesville...
Riverville...
and New Glasgow.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
